    {
      "id": "6a51968b_9ef362d1",
      "file_path": "services/services-onappf/src/main/java/org/onap/policy/apex/services/onappf/handler/ApexEngineHandler.java",
      "patchset_number": 2,
      "line": 99,
      "message": "So we're changing from setting the full list of policies to deploy to doing a delta?\n\nSo if an existing policy is not on either the polsToDeploy or polsToUndeploy lists, it now stays deployed?",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 2787,
        "name": "Liam Fallon",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "liam.fallon@est.tech",
        "username": "liamfallon"
      },
      "updated": "2021-04-15 12:20:35.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": null,
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "id": "550e0cc2_51cfa64e",
      "file_path": "services/services-onappf/src/main/java/org/onap/policy/apex/services/onappf/handler/ApexEngineHandler.java",
      "patchset_number": 2,
      "line": 99,
      "message": "That's correct. \n\nPAP now does the filtering of the policies to eliminate the need for the PDPs to do this any longer. PDPs now just know about the policies to either deploy or undeploy. \n\nSo yes - if a policy is not on either of the deploy or undeploy lists it will remain deployed and untouched.",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 6722,
        "name": "Wayne Dunican",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "wayne.dunican@est.tech",
        "username": "waynedunican"
      },
      "updated": "2021-04-15 12:30:38.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": "6a51968b_9ef362d1",
      "unresolved": true
    },
