      "in_reply_to": null,
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "id": "e9cf9531_26cfd7d6",
      "file_path": "services/services-onappf/src/main/java/org/onap/policy/apex/services/onappf/handler/PdpUpdateMessageHandler.java",
      "patchset_number": 3,
      "line": 150,
      "message": "This condition is okay, because stopping the core engine completely can be done only when there are no policies to run.So, all runningPolicies should be in the undeployed list to stop the engine.",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 4903,
        "name": "Ajith Sreekumar",
        "display_name": "Ajith Sreekumar",
        "email": "ajith.sreekumar@bell.ca",
        "username": "a.sreekumar"
      },
      "updated": "2021-04-26 14:25:37.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": "ebc9ccb2_f02bbaa9",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "id": "202b774a_3b63b6b0",
      "file_path": "services/services-onappf/src/main/java/org/onap/policy/apex/services/onappf/handler/PdpUpdateMessageHandler.java",
      "patchset_number": 3,
      "line": 153,
      "message": "I don't think this is a condition for stopping the engine. What if already some policies are running, and PAP sends a PDP_UPDATE message with both lists empty? In this case, it shouldn't affect the current policies.\nAgree with Jim.",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 4903,
        "name": "Ajith Sreekumar",
        "display_name": "Ajith Sreekumar",
        "email": "ajith.sreekumar@bell.ca",
        "username": "a.sreekumar"
      },
      "updated": "2021-04-26 14:25:37.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": null,
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "id": "666f8456_6fa42cd3",
